Included in the property stolen from the Manhattan Savings Bank, in New-York, recently, was a large number of registered bonds of the United States, valued in all at about $1,600,000. abstract: Secretary Sherman visited the Custom-house yesterday, at 11 A.M. and did not take his departure until 3 P.M. He was accompanied by Treasurer Gilfillan. Collector Merritt, Surveyor Graham, and Naval Officer Burt were summoned into the official presence, and a general discussion took place on matters particularly relating to the working of the present Custom-house system.
